-- Turkish Treasury to Sell 10.8 Billion Liras of Domestic Debt in July
-- Mark Bentley
-- 2010-06-30T14:28:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/turkish-treasury-to-sell-10-8-billion-liras-of-domestic-debt-in-july.html

          
          
             Turkey will sell 10.8 billion liras
($6.8 billion) of domestic debt next month and repay 12.7
billion liras of the local paper, the Treasury said on its Web
site today.  
 The Treasury will sell 651-day zero coupon bonds on July
13, 2013 10 percent fixed interest debt on July 26, 357-day zero
coupon bonds on July 27 and new 2017 floating rate notes the
same day, it said.  
          
          


  


        